Description: CVE-2026-48163 - wsrep_sst_common.sh: harden safe() to reject tab and newline (MDEV-39648)
 OS Command Injection (CWE-78) in MariaDB Galera SST rsync method.
 wsrep_sst_rsync.sh interpolated WSREP_SST_OPT_REMOTE_USER and
 WSREP_SST_OPT_REMOTE_PSWD verbatim into stunnel.conf and the rsync magic
 file; a newline in either could splice an extra directive (silently
 disabling peer-cert verification) on the donor.
 .
 The wsrep_sst_rsync.sh routing through safe() and the accompanying
 galera_sst_rsync_encrypt_with_key_server.{test,result,cnf} regression test
 are already delivered by the combined backport in CVE-2026-44168 (which
 bundles MDEV-39413, MDEV-39648 and MDEV-39721). That backport, however,
 ships the original MDEV-39413 safe() helper, which only rejects spaces,
 single quotes and backticks - it does NOT reject newlines, so the rsync
 newline-splicing vector remains open.
 .
 This patch completes MDEV-39648 by hardening safe() in wsrep_sst_common.sh
 to also reject tab and newline, so multi-line joiner-supplied values cannot
 survive into the config-file heredocs that safe() is meant to guard. It
 applies on top of the safe() helper introduced by CVE-2026-44168.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/dae315a7b2bf8bd2fd0449467e711e5a2db26669
Author: Hemant Dangi <hemant.dangi@mariadb.com>
Last-Update: 2026-06-17
---
--- a/scripts/wsrep_sst_common.sh
+++ b/scripts/wsrep_sst_common.sh
@@ -31,7 +31,7 @@
 safe()
 {
-  if [[ "${!1}" = *[\ \'\`]* ]]; then
+  if [[ "${!1}" = *[\ \'\`$'\t'$'\n']* ]]; then
     wsrep_log_error "Invalid value for $1: ${!1}"
     exit 21
   fi
   echo "${!1}"
Description: Fix CVE-2026-44168 - wsrep unsafe handling of joiner-supplied parameters
 MariaDB wsrep SST scripts (wsrep_sst_common.sh, wsrep_sst_mariabackup.sh,
 wsrep_sst_rsync.sh) and sql/wsrep_notify.cc unsafely interpolate
 joiner-supplied parameters (TLS certificate CommonName,
 WSREP_SST_OPT_REMOTE_USER/PSWD, wsrep_node_name and
 wsrep_node_incoming_address) into shell commands, enabling OS command
 injection (CWE-78) by an authorized cluster peer.
 .
 This backport combines three upstream fixes:
   * MDEV-39413 (3e3c5d72): introduce a safe() shell helper in
     wsrep_sst_common.sh that rejects spaces, single quotes and backticks,
     and route mariabackup SST interpolations through it.
   * MDEV-39648 (dae315a7): apply safe() to joiner-supplied
     WSREP_SST_OPT_REMOTE_USER and WSREP_SST_OPT_REMOTE_PSWD in
     wsrep_sst_rsync.sh so newlines cannot splice extra directives into
     the donor-written stunnel.conf or the rsync magic file.
   * MDEV-39721 (ed8404a7): in sql/wsrep_notify.cc, validate the peer's
     wsrep_node_name and wsrep_node_incoming_address against a narrow
     whitelist before interpolating them into the wsrep_notify_cmd
     command string that is then executed via 'sh -c'.
 .
 SSL test fixture regeneration and the modifications to
 galera_sst_mariabackup_encrypt_with_key_server.{test,result} from the
 upstream commit are intentionally omitted from this backport per the
 research-report recommendation; they are non-essential to the security
 fix and depend on regenerated PEM artifacts.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/3e3c5d72c8fbff5994edcb43d3cf387628de2d32
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/dae315a7b2bf8bd2fd0449467e711e5a2db26669
