Description: CVE-2026-21968 - Fix Optimizer crash/DoS in degenerate JTBM semi-join
 Fixes a vulnerability in the MariaDB Server Optimizer component (MDEV-30721)
 that allows a low-privileged attacker with network access to cause a denial
 of service (complete crash) via a crafted SQL query.
 .
 When processing a degenerate JTBM semi-join (a subquery that produces
 0 or 1 rows), execute_degenerate_jtbm_semi_join() creates equality
 conditions and adds them to eq_list. These equalities are then merged
 with existing conditions via and_new_conditions_to_optimized_cond(),
 creating an Item_cond_and. However, this item was not fixed before being
 walked by is_simplified_cond_processor, which calls val_bool() to check
 if the condition is a known constant. Calling val_bool() on an unfixed
 item triggers an assertion failure (crash).
 .
 The fix moves the fix_fields_if_needed() call to occur immediately after
 the condition is created, before any evaluation or simplification is
 attempted.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/cff68791de82243cde5d1aa11ba37a01fa86d5e6
Bug: https://jira.mariadb.org/browse/MDEV-30721
Author: Oleg Smirnov <oleg.smirnov@mariadb.com>
Last-Update: 2025-10-10

--- a/sql/opt_subselect.cc
+++ b/sql/opt_subselect.cc
@@ -6138,7 +6138,7 @@ Item *and_new_conditions_to_optimized_cond(THD *thd, Item *cond,
     }
   }

-  if (!cond)
+  if (!cond || cond->fix_fields_if_needed(thd, &cond))
     return NULL;

   if (*cond_eq)
@@ -6171,9 +6171,6 @@ Item *and_new_conditions_to_optimized_cond(THD *thd, Item *cond,
   if (cond && is_simplified_cond)
     cond= cond->remove_eq_conds(thd, cond_value, true);

-  if (cond && cond->fix_fields_if_needed(thd, NULL))
-    return NULL;
-
   return cond;
 }
Description: CVE-2026-49261 - wsrep_notify_cmd injection (MDEV-39721) - already fixed by CVE-2026-44168
 wsrep_notify_status() in sql/wsrep_notify.cc interpolated joiner-supplied
 wsrep_node_name and wsrep_node_incoming_address into a command string executed
 via sh -c, enabling OS command injection (CWE-78) when wsrep_notify_cmd is set.
 .
 The upstream fix (commit ed8404a73f93e79aff7227bb4560a44cbfdb5d1c, MDEV-39721)
 adds is_valid_node_name() / is_valid_node_addr() whitelist validators and the
 galera_wsrep_notify_cmd_injection regression test.
 .
 That fix is already included in the combined backport delivered by
 CVE-2026-44168, which bundles MDEV-39413, MDEV-39648 and MDEV-39721 for
 bookworm mariadb 10.11.14. Re-applying the same hunks here fails because
 sql/wsrep_notify.cc and the galera_wsrep_notify_cmd_injection test files
 already exist after CVE-2026-44168 is applied.
 .
 No additional code changes are required for CVE-2026-49261 on this release;
 this hook documents that the vulnerability is remediated via CVE-2026-44168.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/ed8404a73f93e79aff7227bb4560a44cbfdb5d1c
Bug: https://jira.mariadb.org/browse/MDEV-39721
Last-Update: 2026-06-18
