+---
+
+## Summary
+
+CVE-2026-49261 is an OS command injection (CWE-78, CVSS 10.0) in Galera cluster
+notification handling: `wsrep_notify_status()` interpolated joiner-supplied
+`wsrep_node_name` and `wsrep_node_incoming_address` into a command string that
+is executed via `sh -c` when `wsrep_notify_cmd` is configured.
+
+The upstream fix (commit `ed8404a73f93e79aff7227bb4560a44cbfdb5d1c`) adds narrow
+whitelist validators and skips notification on unsafe input.
+
+---
+
+## Why no separate patch is applied here
+
+Debian bookworm's hook for **CVE-2026-44168** is a combined backport that already
+includes MDEV-39721 alongside MDEV-39413 and MDEV-39648. After CVE-2026-44168
+applies, the tree already contains:
+
+- `is_valid_node_name()` / `is_valid_node_addr()` in `sql/wsrep_notify.cc`
+- Validation before interpolating member name/address into `wsrep_notify_cmd`
+- `mysql-test/suite/galera/t/galera_wsrep_notify_cmd_injection.{test,cnf}`
+- `mysql-test/suite/galera/r/galera_wsrep_notify_cmd_injection.result`
+
+A standalone CVE-2026-49261 patch duplicates those exact changes and fails with
+"file already exists" / "Reversed (or previously applied) patch detected".
+
+**CVE-2026-49261 is remediated on this package version via CVE-2026-44168.**
+
+---
+
+## References
+
+- CVE record: https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-49261
+- Upstream fix: https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/ed8404a73f93e79aff7227bb4560a44cbfdb5d1c
+- Jira: https://jira.mariadb.org/browse/MDEV-39721
