Description: Fix CVE-2026-48165 - Galera SST OS command injection
 A high-privileged user could use the wsrep_sst_donor,
 wsrep_sst_method, or wsrep_sst_receive_address global system
 variables to inject and execute shell commands as the uid of the
 mariadbd process on the Galera joiner node (CWE-78). The values
 flowed unvalidated into the shell command line that mariadbd
 builds when invoking the SST helper script.
 .
 This patch verifies that wsrep_sst_donor, wsrep_sst_method, and
 wsrep_sst_receive_address contain only supported characters
 (alphanumerics plus - _ . : [ ] / and, for donor lists, comma).
 NULL or empty values are still rejected for wsrep_sst_donor (the
 follow-up commit re-disallows NULL there because it crashed in
 galera.mdev-28433).
 .
 Combines two upstream MariaDB/server commits (MDEV-39676):
   - 13e6808f0138175ad48bf91b6487f56f33c51919 (primary fix)
   - a9e2f7f648f339c6f49b5bbe0435fa6b04a27ed2 (NULL follow-up)
 Released upstream in 10.11.18, 10.6.27, 11.4.12, 11.8.8, 12.3.2.
